{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"diskInject","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The script runs automatically when macOS starts — no SSH,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"no agent, no network, and no manual setup required. This is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the only provisioning mode that works on a completely vanilla"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS installation from an IPSW."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Before the VM boots, Spooktacular mounts"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the guest’s data volume on the host and writes a standard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS LaunchDaemon that executes your script at boot time."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Best for:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" Fresh VMs created from IPSW where you need"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"zero-touch automation — CI runners, test environments,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"automated fleet provisioning."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Requires:","type":"text"}]},{"text":" Nothing in the guest. Works with any macOS.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Injects a LaunchDaemon into the VM’s disk before first boot.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode\/diskInject"},"kind":"symbol","seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Provi